<doc id="418129" wikidata="Q2528291" url="?curid=418129" title="Vishwanath">
<text>Vishwanath (also spelt Viswanath, Vishvanath, Viswanatha) is an Indian surname and given name. It is of Hindu origin and derives from &quot;višvanatha&quot;, meaning &quot;lord of the universe&quot; (from &quot;višva&quot;, &quot;universe&quot; + &quot;natha&quot;, &quot;lord,&quot; an epithet of the god Shiva), including the Tamil-Malayalam third-person masculine singular suffix -n, -m. It may refer to:

