The boson creation (resp. annihilation) operator is usually denoted as formula_62 (resp. formula_63). The creation operator formula_62 adds a boson to the single-particle state formula_28, and the annihilation operator formula_63 removes a boson from the single-particle state formula_28. The creation and annihilation operators are Hermitian conjugate to each other, but neither of them are Hermitian operators (formula_68).

